From b2c0a91e0000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ETNA <etna@example.com>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix fusion of annotated documents

Synthesised from upstream commit ff555e19b7b1 ("Fix fusion of annotated
documents (#114)"). Reverse-applying this patch reintroduces the bug
where `fuse` for an `Annotated _ Empty` discards the annotation entirely
(returning `Empty`), and otherwise also drops fusion inside annotations.
Renderers that rely on annotation push/pop markers (e.g. terminal
colouring, structured tree rendering) lose annotation boundaries on
documents containing empty annotated children.

---
 prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs b/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs
index 0000000..0000000 100755
--- a/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs
+++ b/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs
@@ -1663,7 +1663,7 @@ fuse depth = go
         Nest 0 x         -> go x
         Nest i x         -> Nest i (go x)

-        Annotated _ Empty -> Empty
+        Annotated ann x -> Annotated ann (go x)

         FlatAlt x1 x2 -> FlatAlt (go x1) (go x2)
         Union x1 x2   -> Union (go x1) (go x2)
